    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 13: FUEL SYSTEM - FUEL SYSTEM</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FUEL SYSTEM</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="16">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using an appropriate filter wrench/strap, loosen and remove the fuel filter from the
                    fuel filter header and discard.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601304">13.4</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        shows the engines equipped with the front mounted hand primer pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601305">13.5</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        shows the engines equipped with the top mounted hand primer pump.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601304" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5107" filename="../figeg5/eg5107.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.4 Remove Fuel Filter On Engines Equipped With Front Mounted Hand Primer
                            Pump
                        </caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601305" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6892" filename="../figeg6/eg6892.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.5 Remove Oil Filter On Engines Equipped With Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump
                        </caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fuel filter strainer as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601306">13.6</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove plastic strainer cover from filter strainer assembly using a 29 mm or 1-1/8
                        inch socket.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Clean or replace strainer after inspection and reinstall strainer and cover to fuel
                        filter header assembly. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">"Installation"</emph>
                        in this section.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>INSTALL STRAINER WITH OPEN END TOWARD FILTER HEADER.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With Front Mounted Hand Primer Pump:</emph>
                    Remove the supply pump inlet fuel line as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601307">13.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove the hollow screws and copper sealing gaskets at the fuel filter
                        header and supply pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With A Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump:</emph>
                    Remove the supply pump inlet fuel line as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601308">13.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen fitting and remove fuel filter header to supply pump line.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601306" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5109" filename="../figeg5/eg5109.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.6 Remove Fuel Strainer Assembly</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">1. Strainer Cover</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">2. O-Ring</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">3. Strainer</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601307" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5112" filename="../figeg5/eg5112.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.7 Remove Fuel Supply Line, Front Mounted Primer Pump</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">1. Transfer Pump</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">2. Fuel Filter Header Inlet Fuel Line</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">3. Fuel Filter Header To Transfer Pump Line</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601308" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6862" filename="../figeg6/eg6862.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.8 Remove Fuel Supply Line, Top Mounted Primer Pump</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With Front Mounted Hand Primer Pump:</emph>
                    Remove the final fuel filter inlet fuel line as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601309">13.9</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove the hollow screws and copper sealing gaskets at fuel filter header
                        and supply pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With A Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump:</emph>
                    Remove the final fuel filter inlet fuel line as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601310">13.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen fitting and remove the final fuel filter inlet fuel line.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With An Engine Mounted ECM Unit:</emph>
                    Remove the final fuel filter inlet fuel line as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601311">13.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen fitting and remove the final fuel filter inlet fuel line.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601309" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5114" filename="../figeg5/eg5114.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.9 Remove Final Fuel Filter, Front Mounted Hand Primer Pump</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601310" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6866" filename="../figeg6/eg6866.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.10 Remove Final Fuel Filter, Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601311" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6887" filename="../figeg6/eg6887.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.11 Remove Final Fuel Filter, On Engines Equipped With An Engine Mounted ECM
                            Unit
                        </caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With Front Mounted Hand Primer Pump:</emph>
                    Disconnect the fuel supply line from the fuel filter header to the supply manifold (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601312">13.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove the hollow screws and copper sealing gaskets at the fuel filter
                        header and supply pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With A Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump:</emph>
                    Disconnect the fuel supply line from the fuel filter header to the supply manifold (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601313">13.13</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen fitting and remove fuel filter header to supply pump line.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On Engines Equipped With An Engine Mounted ECM Unit:</emph>
                    Disconnect the fuel supply line from the fuel filter header to the supply manifold (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601314">13.14</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen fitting and remove fuel filter header to supply pump line.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap the fuel filter header and supply pump openings using
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE4294</emph>.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601312" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5113" filename="../figeg5/eg5113.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.12 Remove Fuel Supply Line, Front Mounted Hand Primer Pump</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601313" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6864" filename="../figeg6/eg6864.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.13 Remove Fuel Supply Line, Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601314" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6885" filename="../figeg6/eg6885.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.14 Remove Fuel Supply Line, On Engines Equipped With An Engine Mounted ECM
                            Unit
                        </caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two (2) mounting bolts which secure the fuel filter header to the
                    crankcase.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601315">13.15</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        shows the fuel filter header on engines equipped with the front mounted hand primer pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601316">13.16</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        shows the fuel filter header on engines equipped with a top mounted hand primer pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601317">13.17</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        shows the fuel filter header on engines equipped with the engine mounted ECM unit.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601315" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5115" filename="../figeg5/eg5115.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.15 Remove Front Mounted Hand Primer Pump</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601316" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6869" filename="../figeg6/eg6869.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.16 Remove Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601317" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6882" filename="../figeg6/eg6882.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.17 Remove Top Mounted Hand Primer Pump On Engines Equipped With Engine
                            Mounted ECM Unit
                        </caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen three (3) bolts securing the supply pump to the high pressure pump. Remove supply
                    pump.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601318">13.18</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        shows the supply pump on engines equipped with the front mounted hand primer pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601319">13.19</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        shows the supply pump on engines equipped with the top mounted hand primer pump.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If it is necessary to remove the supply manifold, refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Section 12, "High Pressure Lube Oil System"</emph>
                    for removal, inspection and assembly procedures.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601318" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5118" filename="../figeg5/eg5118.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13.18 Remove Supply Pump On Engines Equipped With A Front Mounted Hand Primer Pump
                    </caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Supply Pump</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Supply Pump Mounting Bolts (3)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. High Pressure Pump</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1601319" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg6870" filename="../figeg6/eg6870.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13.19 Remove Supply Pump On Engines Equipped With An Engine Mounted ECM Unit
                    </caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Supply Pump Mounting Bolts (3)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Supply Pump</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. High Pressure Pump Oil Supply Line</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
